 is a strongly decreasing function of the intrinsic 2-10 keV\nluminosity, $L_{X}$, where $f_{c}=(-0.41\\pm0.13)$log$_{10}$($L_{X}$/erg\ns$^{-1}$)$+18.31\\pm5.33$, across more than two orders of magnitude in $L_{X}$\n(10$^{41.5}-10^{44}$ erg s$^{-1}$). The covering factors measured here agree\nwell with the obscured fraction as a function of $L_{X}$ as determined by\nstudies of local AGN with $L_{X}>10^{42.5}$ erg s$^{-1}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Feb 2015 21:00:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-27"}
