 low temperature, placing this material\nsimultaneously in both clean and dirty limit. Interestingly, this material\nfalls on the universal scaling line initially observed for the cuprate\nsuperconductors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Feb 2015 15:51:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Apr 2015 20:43:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-14"}
